# XML and Localization Rules

## XML Definition Rules

Follow the existing XML structure and naming conventions:

- **Ability definitions**: Add to [1.5/Defs/AbilityDefs/Soulweaver.xml](mdc:1.5/Defs/AbilityDefs/Soulweaver.xml)
- **Thought definitions**: Add to [1.5/Defs/ThoughtDefs/Soulweaver.xml](mdc:1.5/Defs/ThoughtDefs/Soulweaver.xml)
- **Hediff definitions**: Add to [1.5/Defs/HediffDefs/Soulweaver.xml](mdc:1.5/Defs/HediffDefs/Soulweaver.xml)
- **Sound definitions**: Add to [1.5/Defs/SoundDefs/SoulSerpent.xml](mdc:1.5/Defs/SoundDefs/SoulSerpent.xml)

Ensure proper prerequisites and level progression in psycast paths.

## Language Key Management

**ALWAYS update language keys** when adding or changing validation messages, UI text, or any user-facing strings.

- **Use the "VS." prefix** for all translation keys to maintain consistency
- **Add new keys** to [Languages/English/Keyed/Keys.xml](mdc:Languages/English/Keyed/Keys.xml)
- **Update existing keys** when changing message content
- **Ensure translation keys match exactly** with the language file

## XML Documentation

- Provide clear, descriptive labels and descriptions
- Use consistent terminology across the mod
- Explain the lore and mechanics of new abilities
- Ensure descriptions match the actual implementation




